The paper presents a method for robots to learn manipulation tasks using deep learning and motion planning. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as the focus is on robot manipulation. The method uses RGB-D images, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely category. The use of deep learning also suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as possible categories. Finally, the paper involves the integration of perception and control, which suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as a possible category.
